 boundaries between reality and fantasy, frequently making his reader laugh about the serious while aching when reading the humorous.   aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Jul 2022) 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / General.2bisacsh  aFiction, Latvia, Early 20th century.1 aGulēna, Ilze, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLiepiņa, Anita, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertCentral European University Press eBook-Package 2013-1998z978311078055040uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9786155211997423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9786155211997/original  a978-3-11-078055-0  Central European University Press eBook-Package 2013-1998c1998d2013  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_LT  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_LT  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA5EBK